19#include "ZXContainerAlgorithms.h"
20
21#include <utility>
22#include <vector>
23
24namespace ZXing {
25namespace Pdf417 {
26
27class ModulusGF;
28
29/**
30* @author Sean Owen
31* @see com.google.zxing.common.reedsolomon.GenericGFPoly
32*/
33class ModulusPoly
34{
35 const ModulusGF* _field = nullptr;
36 std::vector<int> _coefficients;
37
38public:
39 // Build a invalid object, so that this can be used in container or return by reference,
40 // any access to invalid object is undefined behavior.
41 ModulusPoly() = default;
42
43 ModulusPoly(const ModulusGF& field, const std::vector<int>& coefficients);
44
45 const std::vector<int>& coefficients() const {
46 return _coefficients;
47 }
48
49 /**
50 * @return degree of this polynomial
51 */
52 int degree() const {
53 return Size(_coefficients) - 1;
54 }
55
56 /**
57 * @return true iff this polynomial is the monomial "0"
58 */
59 bool isZero() const {
60 return _coefficients.at(0) == 0;
61 }
62
63 /**
64 * @return coefficient of x^degree term in this polynomial
65 */
66 int coefficient(int degree) const {
67 return _coefficients.at(_coefficients.size() - 1 - degree);
68 }
69
70 /**
71 * @return evaluation of this polynomial at a given point
72 */
73 int evaluateAt(int a) const;
74
75 ModulusPoly add(const ModulusPoly& other) const;
76 ModulusPoly subtract(const ModulusPoly& other) const;
77 ModulusPoly multiply(const ModulusPoly& other) const;
78 ModulusPoly negative() const;
79 ModulusPoly multiply(int scalar) const;
80 ModulusPoly multiplyByMonomial(int degree, int coefficient) const;
81 void divide(const ModulusPoly& other, ModulusPoly& quotient, ModulusPoly& remainder) const;
82
83 friend void swap(ModulusPoly& a, ModulusPoly& b)
84 {
85 std::swap(a._field, b._field);
86 std::swap(a._coefficients, b._coefficients);
87 }
88};
89
90} // Pdf417
91} // ZXing
